SUPLINF.P:
As required by section 212 of SBREFA, EPA also is preparing a Small Entity Compliance Guide to help small entities comply with this rule. This guide will be available on the RFS Web site (
www.epa.gov/otaq/renewablefuels/index.htm
), and will be available 60 days after the rule is finalized.

This rulemaking changes the Renewable Fuel Standard (RFS) program at Title 40 of the Code of Federal Regulations, Subpart K which already contains voluntary consensus standard ASTM D6751-06a âStandard Specification for Biodiesel Fuel Blend Stock (B100) for Middle Distillate Fuelsâ. This rulemaking incorporates the most recent version of that standard (ASTM D-6751-08) and adds several more voluntary consensus standards: ASTM D-1250-08, âStandard Guide for Use of the Petroleum Measurement Tablesâ; ASTM D-4442, âStandard Test Methods for Direct Moisture Content Measurement of Wood and Wood-Base Materialsâ; ASTM D-4444, âStandard Test Method for Laboratory Standardization and Calibration of Hand-Held Moisture Metersâ; ASTM D-6866-08 âStandard Test Methods for Determining the Biobased Content of Solid, Liquid, and Gaseous Samples Using Radiocarbon Analysisâ; ASTM E-711, âStandard Test Method for Gross Calorific Value of Refuse-Derived Fuel by the Bomb Calorimeterâ; and ASTM E-870, âStandard Test Methods for Analysis of Wood Fuelsâ. Information about these standards may be obtained through the ASTM Web site (
http://www.astm.org
) or by calling ASTM at (610) 832-9585.

